Edition:
Quote:  PUPUHARAKEKE or FLAX SNAIL (<i>Placostylus hongii</i>). ??? to reddish-brown coloured snail about 3 inches in height. These snails are vegetarian and feed largely upon fallen karaka leaves. They are found hidden under leaves and around sedges(?), but only in flax when there is no other cover.
